==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: corncockle
<hw>corncockle</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a European annual
(<spn>Agrostemma githago</spn>) having large trumpet-shaped
reddish-purple flowers and poisonous seed; a common weed in grainfields
and beside roadways; naturalized in America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> corn cockle, corn-cockle, corn campion,
crown-of-the-field, <spn>Agrostemma githago</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corncrake</ent>⟦br⟧
